text: let's talk about money because I don't
like spending it on things I don't need
I am frugal and I've always been that
way regardless of my income right now
we're cruising around Syria Cambodia in
a tuk tuk in early 2015 I left my
teaching English job in South Korea to
travel full time and every year since
then my income has steadily increased
especially over the last six months
since I started utilizing YouTube and
Facebook ads I'm going to make well over
six figures this year I'm not telling
you this to brag but rather I want you
to know that no matter how much money my
bank account shows I will still eat
street food I will still sleep in budget
hotels the cheapest private room I found
online last night in Dubai 38 bucks and
book the cheapest flights I can find I
will still take the metro over a taxi to
order water at restaurants and make
coffee at home these things save me a
lot of money in the long run after all
this is why we moved to Bangkok and not
New York City but don't mistake me being
frugal for being cheap they are very
different I will always give a generous
tip if the service is good I won't ever
steal anything or sneaking snacks to a
sporting event I don't complain about
the price of everything and I will
happily spend a few extra dollars if
that means I'll be saving time being
frugal means that I choose to prioritize
my spending so I can have more of the
things I love like travel I don't need
to buy a big house I literally cannot
believe how big these houses are or a
fancy car or a steak dinner unless of
course it's a special occasion as long
as I can get from point A to point B as
long as I have a roof over my head when
I sleep and as long as I have a plate of
food to eat I'm a happy guy one of my
role models is Warren Buffett he's one
of the most successful investors with a
net worth of 84 billion dollars despite
being the world's third richest man he
is very frugal he lives in a small house
he eats McDonald's every day he doesn't
own a smartphone and he pledged to give
away 99% of his fortune to charities
I love Warren's simple approach to life
and I plan to follow his footsteps to be
honest I feel guilty living a luxurious
life especially when I witnessed some of
the world's most impoverished places
I've learned that had
penis is not always correlated with
money it usually works the other way
around
so instead of buying a nice car I'd
rather give that money to help those in
need because in the end that will make
me the happiest I'm drew pinsky and if
you like my travel videos please click
Subscribe and join me as I plan to visit
every country in the world
